1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:02,240
previously on ghost whisperer...

2
00:00:02,340 --> 00:00:03,310
we're getting ready.

3
00:00:03,410 --> 00:00:05,710
For what?
- For what's coming.

4
00:00:06,420 --> 00:00:08,720
It's time for you
to know who you are.

5
00:00:08,990 --> 00:00:10,920
And to know who your brother is.

6
00:00:11,020 --> 00:00:12,890
Do you really think it was
your father in the light?

7
00:00:12,990 --> 00:00:15,290
If he's dead, I have to
find out what happened.

8
00:00:18,720 --> 00:00:21,060
You are so over your head.

9
00:00:21,210 --> 00:00:23,010
And I really wouldn't come back.

10
00:00:23,110 --> 00:00:25,410
Ever.

11
00:00:28,090 --> 00:00:30,210
All right, I get it.

12
00:00:30,310 --> 00:00:32,240
I understand.

13
00:00:32,340 --> 00:00:33,870
I'll make dinner.

14
00:00:33,970 --> 00:00:36,860
I'll do the dishes, but, uh,

15
00:00:37,190 --> 00:00:39,490
you just relax. Take it easy.

16
00:00:39,890 --> 00:00:41,970
Look, I offered to help.

17
00:00:42,070 --> 00:00:43,210
Did I miss that?

18
00:00:43,310 --> 00:00:45,900
Look at me. Doing my part,
going to get the door.

19
00:00:46,020 --> 00:00:48,320
Don't hurt your hand on
the doorknob. Take it easy.

20
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:53,940
Mel, who is it?

21
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:02,960
What the hell are you doing here?

22
00:01:04,340 --> 00:01:05,320
Wow.

23
00:01:05,420 --> 00:01:07,720
You're angry.

24
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:10,620
I was there when you got hurt.

25
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:11,663
You think it's my fault.

26
00:01:11,762 --> 00:01:14,960
You were there, smiling,
and she wasn't just hurt.

27
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:17,880
For the longest minute
of my life, she was dead.

28
00:01:17,990 --> 00:01:19,280
Yeah.

29
00:01:19,380 --> 00:01:21,450
You know, a part of me didn't
mind seeing you like that.

30
00:01:21,550 --> 00:01:25,680
For a very long time I blamed my entire
family for leaving me locked up in that...

31
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:28,320
where I grew up.
- Too bad.

32
00:01:28,420 --> 00:01:30,010
Go.
- I'm trying to find dad.

33
00:01:30,110 --> 00:01:31,390
Mine or yours?

34
00:01:31,490 --> 00:01:32,580
Ours.

35
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,940
My father's dead.

36
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:35,890
Why should that keep either
of us from looking for him?

37
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:37,710
We both see ghosts.
- Are you done?

38
00:01:37,810 --> 00:01:40,110
Look, I...

39
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:44,120
I figured you'd still be in denial.

40
00:01:44,220 --> 00:01:47,250
Who would want to admit that their old
man had an extra family on the side?

41
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:50,050
But are you gonna tell
me you haven't seen him?

42
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:52,780
He hasn't come to visit
you in your dreams?

43
00:01:54,660 --> 00:01:56,340
Yeah, I thought so.

44
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:58,620
He's been haunting my dreams, too.

45
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,250
How do you think I found
out you were my sister?

46
00:02:00,350 --> 00:02:02,340
Jim asked you to leave, nicely.

47
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:04,140
What are you hiding from?

48
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,470
We're both trying to find him.

49
00:02:05,570 --> 00:02:07,120
We both have unfinished
business with him.

50
00:02:07,220 --> 00:02:08,480
We... we should be
working together...

51
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:10,540
that's enough! Go!

52
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:12,030
Look.

53
00:02:12,130 --> 00:02:14,430
My mother gave this
to me when I was a kid.

54
00:02:14,990 --> 00:02:17,290
It belonged to my dad.

55
00:02:17,450 --> 00:02:19,770
It'll mean a lot more to
you than it ever did to me.

56
00:02:22,770 --> 00:02:24,670
Patient Personal Property

57
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:26,540
For you, they were family.

58
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:29,430
For me, they were just more
people he had to hide me from.

59
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:32,270
Where was your mother for all this?

60
00:02:32,370 --> 00:02:33,960
She was always close by.

61
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:36,360
In the next ward
the mental hospital

62
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:46,860
This is my dad's parents
right after they got married.

63
00:02:49,050 --> 00:02:50,870
And, uh,

64
00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:52,915
my dad told me that
he got these cufflinks

65
00:02:53,015 --> 00:02:55,870
from his aunt and uncle right
after he graduated college.

66
00:02:55,980 --> 00:02:58,660
Honey, you know, gabriel could have
gotten this stuff from anywhere.

67
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,160
I don't trust him either.

68
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:01,440
But

69
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:05,370
I just can't shake the feeling that he might
be telling the truth about being my brother.

70
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:06,570
Why do you think that?

71
00:03:06,670 --> 00:03:08,720
Too many coincidences.

72
00:03:08,820 --> 00:03:12,160
Gabriel showed up right after
that dad told me I had brother.

73
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:15,740
And let's face it... my dad was

74
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:18,250
in and out of the house
for a lot of years,

75
00:03:18,350 --> 00:03:21,780
so he could have had kids,
and I wouldn't have known.

76
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:27,220
Gabriel didn't get his gift from
dad, but he got other things.

77
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:32,240
Well, he certainly got your dad's
gift for tying you up in knots.

78
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:38,160
I left the lights on downstairs.
I'm going to turn 'em off.

79
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:39,940
You need anything? Tea? Water?

80
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:42,340
No.
- Ok.

81
00:04:24,670 --> 00:04:26,220
So who do you think
the picture's of?

82
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,220
It's gotta be some
relative of my dad'S.

83
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:29,600
I mean, all these photos are his.

84
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:31,240
Well, so gabriel says.

85
00:04:31,340 --> 00:04:34,130
Don't worry. I'm not taking
anything gabriel says on faith.

86
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:36,458
I just faxed a request
for his medical records to

87
00:04:36,557 --> 00:04:38,698
that mental institution
he said he grew up in.

88
00:04:38,797 --> 00:04:40,190
"Trust, but verify. "

89
00:04:40,290 --> 00:04:42,990
Yeah, sounds good. Only my
motto is slightly different.

90
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:45,420
Trust, but caffeinate.
What will it be?

91
00:04:45,550 --> 00:04:47,590
The usual. Twice the foam, please.

92
00:04:47,690 --> 00:04:49,990
Ok.

93
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:15,130
Hello?

94
00:05:19,010 --> 00:05:21,860
Who's there?
- Shh!

95
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,540
Who are you?

96
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:26,750
Why are you here?
- Please. Quiet.

97
00:05:27,580 --> 00:05:29,880
They're everywhere.

98
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:32,460
Who?

99
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,860
They told me I was crazy.

100
00:05:35,390 --> 00:05:37,660
They took my baby.

101
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:39,010
Who are you?

102
00:05:39,110 --> 00:05:41,410
What's your name?

103
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:48,600
Wait a minute.

104
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:51,810
Gabriel gave this to me, and he...

105
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:55,420
he said that his mother was
in the same hospital he was.

106
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:59,960
You're gabriel's
mother, aren't you?

107
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:09,970
Help me!

108
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:12,370
Help me!

109
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:51,230
First it was ray billings, then there was
the stalker guy I saw get sucked under,

110
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:53,280
and now this one, gabriel's mother.

111
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:57,240
Well, if you're asking me to tell you that
there are no dark spirits under grandview,

112
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:59,810
get comfortable,'cause
it's gonna be a long wait.

113
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:02,980
You've taken all of the smug
certainty out of being a skeptic.

114
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,120
I'm waiting for you to
tell me how they work.

115
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:08,950
How can dark spirits trap other
ghosts, and why are they underground?

116
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:11,150
Well?

117
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:12,960
Oh, sorry, I thought
we were waiting.

118
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:16,860
Look, the basic gist of it is that the
dark spirits feed on the darker emotions...

119
00:07:16,980 --> 00:07:19,700
hate, anger, fear, jealousy,
greed, all of that stuff.

120
00:07:19,820 --> 00:07:22,690
And it's very powerful emotion,
so it's hard to break their grip.

121
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,980
Yeah, but not impossible?

122
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:25,270
No, it's not impossible.

123
00:07:25,370 --> 00:07:27,670
The things that better them are the
same things that better them in life.

124
00:07:27,790 --> 00:07:28,670
All the good stuff...

125
00:07:28,770 --> 00:07:31,470
love, joy, happiness,
forgiveness, melted cheese,

126
00:07:31,610 --> 00:07:34,060
6
- way adjustable bucket seats, that dress...

127
00:07:34,710 --> 00:07:36,230
great. Thanks.
- Where are you going?

128
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:38,740
You're not actually going to go through with this, are you?
- Why wouldn't I?

129
00:07:38,860 --> 00:07:40,150
You're going to take
a tip from this...

130
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:43,540
this gabriel guy to go find
your untrustworthy deadbeat dad?

131
00:07:43,670 --> 00:07:45,560
Your untrustworthy
deadbeat dead dad?

132
00:07:45,660 --> 00:07:47,070
I'm simply following some leads.

133
00:07:47,170 --> 00:07:48,770
Leads? How? Think about this.

134
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:51,170
I will. Don't worry.

135
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:55,260
I'm worried.

136
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,550
Hey.

137
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,950
I got your call. What's up?

138
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:09,010
I was trying to summon
gabriel's mother...

139
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:10,940
if that's who she is...

140
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:13,340
and while I was
waiting, I got this.

141
00:08:15,050 --> 00:08:17,660
It's the treatment records from
gabriel's institution, correct?

142
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:21,660
Yeah, I asked the doctor for
copies,'cause I wanted to know the truth.

143
00:08:23,330 --> 00:08:25,600
Melinda, look, I'm sorry.

144
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:28,400
I know that I can't imagine
what this feels like for you,

145
00:08:28,530 --> 00:08:31,410
but there's nothing in here
you didn't already know,

146
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:34,580
outside of the fact that
he attacked other patients.

147
00:08:34,710 --> 00:08:37,010
He told them he could see ghosts.

148
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:40,070
They thought he was crazy.

149
00:08:40,170 --> 00:08:42,470
It's why they put him in there.

150
00:08:43,460 --> 00:08:45,240
That could have been me.

151
00:08:45,340 --> 00:08:46,860
No, you have a gift.

152
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,240
He is violent. He is mentally ill.

153
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:50,640
He's my brother. We have
a lot of the same genes.

154
00:08:50,810 --> 00:08:52,290
You don't know that yet.

155
00:08:52,390 --> 00:08:54,690
Actually, I do.

156
00:08:56,250 --> 00:09:00,830
That's why dr. Lawrence wanted
to see my birth certificate.

157
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:04,050
He needed proof that I
was family, and he got it.

158
00:09:05,090 --> 00:09:07,390
Gabriel's father was tom gordon.

159
00:09:08,650 --> 00:09:10,950
He's my half brother.

160
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:14,300
And now you want to save him?

161
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,920
After what he did?

162
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:18,320
But this is what I do.

163
00:09:19,380 --> 00:09:22,980
I help people fix
their worst mistakes.

164
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:36,795
Yes, hello.

165
00:09:36,895 --> 00:09:40,450
Um, you have a guest staying with
you under the name gabriel gordon?

166
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,350
Well, could you check?

167
00:09:44,450 --> 00:09:46,750
Sure. Thanks.

168
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:00,953
Hello?

169
00:10:01,052 --> 00:10:02,473
Mr. Gordon is not answering.

170
00:10:02,572 --> 00:10:03,628
would you like to leave a message?

171
00:10:03,727 --> 00:10:05,220
Yeah!

172
00:10:05,319 --> 00:10:06,743
No.

173
00:10:06,842 --> 00:10:10,300
You know what? I'll... I'll
call back later, thanks.

174
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:21,058
So this wasn't a haunting,
it was more like a vision?

175
00:10:21,157 --> 00:10:22,303
Uh, yeah.

176
00:10:22,402 --> 00:10:26,018
Sometimes I get them, and
ghosts try to show me things,

177
00:10:26,117 --> 00:10:27,900
and I don't always know why.

178
00:10:27,999 --> 00:10:29,748
But it felt like it was real?

179
00:10:29,847 --> 00:10:30,663
Oh, very.

180
00:10:30,762 --> 00:10:33,213
My heart was still
pounding an hour later.

181
00:10:33,312 --> 00:10:35,528
And did you get a chance
to talk to gabriel about it?

182
00:10:35,627 --> 00:10:36,383
No.

183
00:10:36,482 --> 00:10:38,203
The thing is this... this vision,

184
00:10:38,302 --> 00:10:41,588
it was like... I think it's something
that happened to the ghost...

185
00:10:41,687 --> 00:10:43,333
gabriel's mother...
and I, you know,

186
00:10:43,432 --> 00:10:45,278
at first, I thought it maybe
was the moment that they

187
00:10:45,377 --> 00:10:47,328
took her to the hospital,
but that wasn't right.

188
00:10:47,427 --> 00:10:49,160
I mean, these guys
were rough, you know?

189
00:10:49,259 --> 00:10:50,923
They had a big axe
with blood on it.

190
00:10:51,022 --> 00:10:54,078
Right. Bloody axe doesn't
really say hospital, does it?

191
00:10:54,177 --> 00:10:55,993
I have to find out more
before I talk to gabriel,

192
00:10:56,092 --> 00:11:00,588
which is my roundabout way of
asking you to please watch the store.

193
00:11:00,687 --> 00:11:03,348
Only if you promise to
tell me everything you find.

194
00:11:03,447 --> 00:11:05,715
Deal.
- Ok.

195
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:08,723
I'm not hurt.

196
00:11:08,822 --> 00:11:09,998
Uh, just so you know.

197
00:11:10,097 --> 00:11:11,238
I'm bigger than that.

198
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,913
Ok. Good.

199
00:11:13,012 --> 00:11:14,343
I'm a talker. I know I talk a lot.

200
00:11:14,442 --> 00:11:17,093
I can't expect people to listen
to every single word I say,

201
00:11:17,192 --> 00:11:19,808
and that's why it didn't surprise
me you didn't listen to me.

202
00:11:19,907 --> 00:11:22,053
What do you mean? I listened.
- You listened?

203
00:11:22,152 --> 00:11:25,728
Then why are we down here with all of
these creepy, spooky ghosts where they live?

204
00:11:25,827 --> 00:11:29,298
Because you had some advice
from your evil twin half brother.

205
00:11:29,397 --> 00:11:30,683
Look, it was your idea.

206
00:11:30,782 --> 00:11:33,783
You said that we needed to
check all the town death records

207
00:11:33,882 --> 00:11:36,848
and that any place where there
was a dark spirit infestation

208
00:11:36,947 --> 00:11:38,510
would probably have
a lot of deaths.

209
00:11:38,609 --> 00:11:40,138
No, no, no. Not...
not a lot of deaths.

210
00:11:40,237 --> 00:11:41,860
A lot and lot of deaths.

211
00:11:41,959 --> 00:11:43,548
And grisly, awful deaths.

212
00:11:43,647 --> 00:11:44,473
And simultaneous.

213
00:11:44,572 --> 00:11:46,303
Like they all happened
at the same time.

214
00:11:46,402 --> 00:11:48,673
Ok, so shouldn't we check
the records like you said?

215
00:11:48,772 --> 00:11:51,008
All right, I don't like
being quoted back to myself.

216
00:11:51,107 --> 00:11:51,893
Especially when I'm right.

217
00:11:51,992 --> 00:11:54,348
While we are looking, why
don't you go that direction,

218
00:11:54,447 --> 00:11:55,628
and I will go this way?

219
00:11:55,727 --> 00:11:57,980
Ok.

220
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:00,380
Let's see.

221
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:02,638
I've been looking for
you. Where have you been?

222
00:12:02,737 --> 00:12:03,783
Quiet.

223
00:12:03,882 --> 00:12:05,153
They can hear you.

224
00:12:05,252 --> 00:12:06,223
Please tell me what happened.

225
00:12:06,322 --> 00:12:08,518
I can help you cross
over into the light.

226
00:12:08,617 --> 00:12:09,883
Oh, no, no.

227
00:12:09,982 --> 00:12:11,068
I... I can't do that.

228
00:12:11,167 --> 00:12:12,093
I can'T.

229
00:12:12,192 --> 00:12:14,518
I... I don't deserve to be free.

230
00:12:14,617 --> 00:12:16,773
Why?

231
00:12:16,872 --> 00:12:18,953
I lost my baby.

232
00:12:19,052 --> 00:12:21,063
It's all my fault.

233
00:12:21,162 --> 00:12:23,778
What do you mean? What happened?

234
00:12:23,877 --> 00:12:26,458
They all died because of me.

235
00:12:26,557 --> 00:12:28,820
Who?

236
00:12:28,919 --> 00:12:31,113
Give up.

237
00:12:31,212 --> 00:12:32,978
You won't find what
you're looking for.

238
00:12:33,077 --> 00:12:34,608
And what am I looking for?

239
00:12:34,707 --> 00:12:35,553
It doesn't matter.

240
00:12:35,652 --> 00:12:37,518
Whatever it is, you won't find it.

241
00:12:37,617 --> 00:12:38,773
That's my job.

242
00:12:38,872 --> 00:12:43,460
I make sure what's
buried stays that way.

243
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,768
Oh, my god.

244
00:12:54,867 --> 00:12:56,850
What are these?

245
00:12:56,949 --> 00:12:59,217
These are teeth.

246
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:04,003
"Clay 48"?What does that mean?

247
00:13:04,102 --> 00:13:08,868
I don't know, but whoever these belonged
to is going to have a hard time eating beef.

248
00:13:08,967 --> 00:13:10,858
She said they all
died because of me.

249
00:13:10,957 --> 00:13:12,050
Who?
- The ghost.

250
00:13:12,149 --> 00:13:13,266
Gabriel's mother.

251
00:13:13,365 --> 00:13:14,413
You think she... what?

252
00:13:14,512 --> 00:13:15,528
She killed all these people?

253
00:13:15,627 --> 00:13:16,493
I don't know.

254
00:13:16,592 --> 00:13:19,890
But what does she have to
do with all these deaths?

255
00:13:22,730 --> 00:13:24,823
You gave those things to find dad.

256
00:13:24,922 --> 00:13:28,628
Is it just about dad, or are you
looking for someone else, too?

